alert.note: Alert for Grays Harbor (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 05 at 10:33AM PST until December 06 at 9:53AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... Satsop River Near Satsop affecting Grays Harbor County. .Heavy rain over the south slopes of the Olympics will come to an end late this morning. For the Olympic Peninsula Region...including Satsop...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Satsop River near Satsop. * WHEN...Until late tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 38.0 feet, the Satsop River will flood low pasture lands and some roads along the river. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:15 AM PST Tuesday the stage was 39.3 feet. - Flood stage is 38.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 10:15 AM PST Tuesday was 39.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to crest near 35.5 ft. before noon. It will then fall below flood stage late tonight and continue falling. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this evening at 645 PM PST.
